1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Welcome, you do not know how glad I am that you are all here today.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,000
I am Cero, member of Organization ADN.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:14,000
For a long time in the Organization we have been investigating what it is that makes some human groups

4
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:17,000
able to go further than the rest.

5
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:22,000
Why are there teams that together can achieve feats that seem impossible?

6
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Thousands of years ago,

7
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:30,000
humanity already showed what it can do when many people share a common goal.

8
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Colossal works,

9
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:35,000
legacies that still amaze us today.

10
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:36,000
Among them all,

11
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:39,000
one rises as a symbol of balance,

12
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:41,000
effort and precision,

13
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:42,000
the pyramid.

14
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,000
And we have spent years studying patterns,

15
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:48,000
cross-referencing data and exploring the mysteries of human creativity,

16
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:50,000
with an ambitious objective,

17
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:53,000
to understand and recover the extraordinary creative capacity

18
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:56,000
that flourished in the era of the pyramids.

19
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:57,000
Today, at last,

20
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:00,000
we can say that this effort has borne fruit.

21
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:03,000
We have identified a very small number of groups

22
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:06,000
that possess truly exceptional potential.

23
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:08,000
And you,

24
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:10,000
are among them.

25
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Today we will evaluate your skills as a team

26
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:15,000
and you will have to overcome a series of trials

27
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:18,000
to build your own pyramid.

28
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:21,000
A construction made of coordination,

29
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:22,000
ingenuity,

30
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:24,000
and trust.

31
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,000
To overcome these trials,

32
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:28,000
you will need the ten terminals

33
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,000
distributed around the room

34
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:33,000
and some pyramid tokens that we will hand out to you.

35
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:36,000
These tokens will be non-transferable.

36
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,000
To use them,

37
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:39,000
you must place them on the square mark

38
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:42,000
on the upper part of the terminals.

39
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,000
A warning:

40
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:46,000
we do not allow interference here.

41
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Mobile phones and external accessories

42
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:50,000
are forbidden.

43
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,000
Your only tools

44
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:53,000
will be what you have in front of you

45
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:56,000
and your ability to collaborate.

46
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:57,000
For now,

47
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:59,000
this is all I can tell you.

48
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,000
Show me you are a capable team.

49
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:04,000
The test begins now.
